{
  "texts": [
    "Simulation of different SV types using SURVIVOR.",
    "SURVIVOR 56 (version 1.0.7) was used to simulate SV types not covered by the GIAB and other benchmarks.",
    "For this benchmark, 3,000 duplications, inversions and translocations were each simulated within a length range of 500 bp to 30 kb on the human reference genome GRCh37 in diploid mode.",
    "A total sequencing depth of 30× was simulated for ONT reads, with the error profile obtained using the SURVIVOR scanreads command from the HG002 ONT Q20+ dataset.",
    "SVs were called using each SV caller for the simulated reads using the default parameters and post-processing steps also used in the GIAB and other benchmarks (see respective Methods subsections)."
  ]
}